Type Parameters:
E - The type of element managed by this collection.
All Implemented Interfaces:
Composite<Sequence<E>>, Sequential<E>, Comparable<Sequence<E>>, Iterable<E>
public class Queue<E> extends ClosedCollection<E>
This collection class implements a queue (FIFO) data structure. Normally, multiple threads will be accessing a queue at the same time. This class enforces synchronized access to all methods of this class. The implementation dynamically scales up and down the size of the underlying data structures as the number elements changes over time.
Author:
Derk Norton

    • addElement

      public final void addElement(E element) throws InterruptedException
      This method adds a new element to the tail of the queue. If the queue is currently at capacity this method will block until the capacity drops.
      Parameters:
      element - The new element to be added.
      Throws:
      InterruptedException - The thread that was waiting to add an element was interrupted.

    • removeElement

      public final E removeElement() throws InterruptedException
      This method removes the next element from the head of the queue. If the queue is empty, the method blocks until an element is available.
      Returns:
      The head element in the queue.
      Throws:
      InterruptedException - The thread that was waiting to remove an element was interrupted.

    • getHead

      public final E getHead()
      This method returns a reference to the element at the head of the queue without removing the element from the queue.
      Returns:
      The head element in the queue, or null if the queue is empty.
